The minus was for the slightly worn out chair in the room, a bath towel that had seen better days, and the rather high parking rate - $30/night.	The first night my room overlooked a parking lot, and even though it was a fifth floor room, it felt like I was looking into the headlights.	The room was well appointed, with an excellent mini bar, soft robes, slipper socks for chilly feet (purchase), and quality toiletry items.	Although the bed was comfortable, it was noisy and squeaky for two, and we needed an extra blanket.	The room and the bathroom we had, were quite small and dark, with an uninteresting view from the window.